general opening reply
- hit on opponent's side
- hit on 5-point or 4-point
- make a point in usual way
- hit twice
- mirror
- split back to try for advanced anchor
- if opponent split, beware indirect shots
- beware coming under the gun

gammon-go opening reply (aggresive)
- bring builders into play quickly, splitting less important
- hit
- make home-board points
gammon-save opening reply (defensive)
- advanced anchor
- split back checkers for this
